-- Infrastucture Development Hires Morgan Stanley, Credit Suisse for Sale
-- Ruth David
-- 2010-06-24T09:38:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/infrastucture-development-hires-morgan-stanley-credit-suisse-for-sale.html

          
          
             Morgan Stanley and Credit Suisse
Group AG are among four banks that have been hired to manage a
share sale of about $750 million by  Infrastructure Development
Finance Co. , two people with knowledge of the matter said.  
 CLSA India Ltd. and IDFC Capital Ltd. were also appointed
for the proposed sale to institutional investors, the people
said, declining to be identified before a public announcement.
India’s largest lender for ports and roads is scheduled to hold
a shareholders’ meeting on June 28.  
 The board of Mumbai-based  Infrastructure Development  on
April 27 approved plans to raise as much as 35 billion rupees
($755 million) to fund expansion, according to a statement to
the Bombay Stock Exchange. The funds would be raised by selling
equity or equity-linked securities over the next twelve months,
the company said at that time.  
 Vikram Limaye , executive director at Infrastructure
Development, didn’t answer calls to his mobile phone and didn’t
respond immediately to an e-mail seeking comment.  
 Simone Wheeler , CLSA’s spokeswoman in Hong Kong, didn’t
respond to e-mailed queries.  Nick Footitt , Morgan Stanley’s Hong
Kong-based spokesman, couldn’t immediately confirm. Mona Mohan,
a spokeswoman at IDFC, and  Josephine Lee , a spokeswoman for
Credit Suisse, declined to comment.  
